    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: v0.5.0-dev+1342-gde96626ad\r\n\r\nFrom `:h fold-foldcolumn`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nWhere the fold column is too narrow to display all nested folds, digits are\r\nshown to indicate the nesting level.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there any way to disable the numbers showing up ? With `:set fillchars+=foldopen:\\ ,foldsep:\\ ,foldclose:` (i.e. show an indicator only if there are folded lines, à la vscode if you will) and `:set foldcolumn=1` this is how it looks:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot_2021-06-08_22-48-46](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23398472/121229527-b49bbc00-c8ab-11eb-98fe-47a4e74c8623.png)\r\n\r\nIt's also very distracting placed next to the number column (the current line in the screenshot is actually 83; the 3 in front is showing the nested folding level).",
